.TH "clean_cache_range" 9 "clean_cache_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clean_cache_range \- write back a cache range with CLWB
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clean_cache_range
.BI "(void *addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to write back
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write back a cache range using the CLWB (cache line write back)
instruction. Note that \fIsize\fP is internally rounded up to be cache
line size aligned.
